    <h2>School Code of Conduct</h2>
    <p>Welcome to the official Code of Conduct page. The rules outlined here are designed to create a safe and respectful environment for all students, teachers, and staff. Please read them carefully and adhere to them at all times.</p>
    
    <h3>General Behavior Guidelines</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Respect all members of the school community, including students, teachers, and staff.</li>
        <li>Follow the instructions of teachers and staff without question.</li>
        <li>Maintain a positive attitude and help create a supportive environment for learning.</li>
        <li>Follow school rules and regulations at all times.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Classroom Etiquette</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Arrive on time and be prepared for class with necessary materials.</li>
        <li>Participate actively in discussions and activities.</li>
        <li>Refrain from disruptive behavior, including talking during lessons or using mobile phones.</li>
        <li>Respect the property of others and the classroom environment.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Dress Code</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Students should wear the prescribed school uniform during school hours.</li>
        <li>Clothing should be clean, neat, and appropriate for the school environment.</li>
        <li>Clothing with offensive language, images, or slogans is not permitted.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Respect for Property</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Do not damage or deface school property, including books, desks, and equipment.</li>
        <li>Take care of personal belongings and respect the belongings of others.</li>
        <li>Report any damage or maintenance issues to the school staff immediately.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Use of Technology</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Students are expected to use technology responsibly for academic purposes.</li>
        <li>Inappropriate use of the internet or social media on school devices is prohibited.</li>
        <li>Mobile phones should be kept in silent mode and used only during breaks unless otherwise permitted by a teacher.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Consequences for Misconduct</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Failure to adhere to the Code of Conduct may result in disciplinary action, including warnings, detention, suspension, or expulsion, depending on the severity of the violation.</li>
        <li>Students have the right to appeal any disciplinary action through the school’s formal grievance process.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Final Remarks</h3>
    <p>By following these guidelines, we can all contribute to making this school a better place to learn and grow. If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to speak with a teacher or school administrator.</p>
